All <link:internal>GXT</link:internal> widgets are found under this package com.extjs.<link:internal>gxt</link:internal>.ui.client.widget

<link:internal>GXT</link:internal> widgets use Component as base class.
If sizing and positioning is required, then they extend from BoxComponent.

Component extends the widget class, this allows you to use <link:internal>GXT</link:internal> widgets in <link:internal>GWT</link:internal> applications.
Components added to <link:internal>GXT</link:internal> panels will be rendered when inserted!

Can obtain EL object from Component for DOM manipulation.

<link:internal>GWT</link:internal> Component created on setElement(Element) call.
<link:internal>GXT</link:internal> is created on onRender() call.

Pre-render attributes are some visual aspects, features , required to render.

Events =========================

com.extjs.<link:internal>gxt</link:internal>.ui.client.event base events and listener classes

Component.addListener() to add all events in <link:internal>GXT</link:internal>.

Events extend BaseEvent, and may support setCancelled() to cancel an event and its action.
Ex: for BeforeHide event, event.setCancelled(true), will not hide the Window.

Sinking:
Sink the events for widgets that dont have support for events you are interested in.
Ex: <link:internal>Html</link:internal> widget, onmouseover event.
Sink events during or after rendering the widget.
<link:internal>Html</link:internal> text = new <link:internal>Html</link:internal>("I will highlight on hover") {
	protected void onRender(Element target, int index) {
		super.onRender(target, index);
		el().addEventsSunk(Event.MOUSEEVENTS);
	}
};

LayoutContainer:
Automatic Layout capability, can work with various LayoutManagers, default is FlowLayout.
Extended by other containers.

"Unless LayoutContainer is placed within an existing container (with an appropriate layout
manager), you must size the container and call layout() to render its children "
