HorizontalPanel and verticalPanel=======================
uses HTMLtable.
TableRowLayout and TableLayout respectively
Can user tabledata
setWidth()-&gt; set width of the panel
setTableWidth -&gt;Set the width of the table inside, this is in % of the panel size.
!!!!!!!!!!!!!!# setting the table width is very necessary!!!!


====	ContentPanel	====
-Application oriented user interfaces.
Contains
-Button bar
-Support for <link:internal>top</link:internal> and bottom components
-Separate header, footer and body sections
-Header support icon, text and buttons
-Body can be expanded and collapsed

====	Viewport	====
	Extends LayoutContainer, fill's browser window and monitors resizing
	When browser window is resized, Viewport executes its layout, causing children to resize and adjust to the new window dimensions

====	Window		====
Similar functionality to ContentPanel as it extends ContentPanel.
Can be modal, shown, hidden, maximized, restored.
When show() is called it adds itseld to DOM and sets the z-index to be topmost.
Need not add to any container.
To resuse the window object, you should hide it, rather than closing and releasing it.

====	Dialog		====
Dialog extends Window to provide some convenience methods to add buttons and handling them.
Way to build window with ok,cancel,yes, buttons.
HideOnButtonClick hides the dialog after the user clicks the button.
setButtons(Dialog.YESNOCANCEL)
addText("lorem ipsum")


====	MessageBox	====
Similar in behavior to javascript's Window.alert()
Pops up a modal dialog, icon, and a message



